1.00	Shezbi	Rav Shizbi	R. Shezbi (or R. Shezbi; Hebrew: רב שיזבי) was a second generetion Amora sage of Babylon, and a pupil of Rav Chisda. He was known to be a "Great Man" ("Gadol Ba-Torah)", an erudite Torah scholar sage, and when he used to state biblical exegesis that were hard to understand, Rava would warn not underestimate his words and to carefully review them, for they were uttered by a "Great Man".	
